messages.content: The Northwind Health Plus plan provides essential health benefits, including ambulatory patient services, hospitalization, maternity and newborn care, preventive and wellness services, mental health and substance abuse services, and prescription drugs [doc1]. The plan also offers coverage for mental health and substance abuse services that is comparable to medical and surgical benefits [doc1]. It is important to note that the plan must comply with applicable laws and regulations, and cannot discriminate against individuals based on their medical condition or health status [doc1]. If you have any concerns about your coverage, you can contact your Northwind Health Plus plan administrator [doc3].
